  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. However, several mitigating factors must be considered when determining the appropriate sentence. The defendant has no prior criminal record and has already made partial restitution, demonstrating remorse and a willingness to make amends. The courtroom outburst suggesting a 10-year sentence is entirely irrelevant and holds no legal standing in this court. Balancing the need for accountability with the defendant's potential for rehabilitation, a moderate period of incarceration is appropriate, followed by supervised probation and a mandate to complete full restitution.",
